{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0192Yh76Yw8q68ntLQTgeChs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1вҶ’# Self-Evolution System Implementation Plan\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’**Goal:** Implement a daemon-side post-run evolution pipeline that analyzes workflow history to automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows.\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’**Architecture:** Multi-stage LLM pipeline (Collector вҶ’ Classifier вҶ’ Reflector вҶ’ Executor branches) running in the daemon after each workflow completion. Three executor branches: Prompt Curator (ACE-style), Script Generator (LLM code gen), DSL Mutator (deterministic Go). Changes auto-applied with JSONL audit trail and snapshots.\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’**Tech Stack:** Go, SQLite, gRPC, TOML config (`github.com/BurntSushi/toml`), existing LLM agent invocation pattern.\n    10вҶ’\n    11вҶ’**Design doc:** `docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’---\n    14вҶ’\n    15вҶ’## Task 1: Extend Domain Types\n    16вҶ’\n    17вҶ’**Files:**\n    18вҶ’- Modify: `internal/domain/run.go`\n    19вҶ’- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow.go`\n    20вҶ’- Test: `internal/domain/run_test.go`\n    21вҶ’\n    22вҶ’**Step 1: Write failing test for Run.ProjectDir**\n    23вҶ’\n    24вҶ’Add to `internal/domain/run_test.go`:\n    25вҶ’\n    26вҶ’```go\n    27вҶ’func TestRunProjectDir(t *testing.T) {\n    28вҶ’\tr := NewRun(\"test-1\", \"develop\")\n    29вҶ’\tr.ProjectDir = \"/home/user/project\"\n    30вҶ’\tassert.Equal(t, \"/home/user/project\", r.ProjectDir)\n    31вҶ’}\n    32вҶ’```\n    33вҶ’\n    34вҶ’**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n    35вҶ’\n    36вҶ’Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\n    37вҶ’Expected: FAIL вҖ” `r.ProjectDir undefined`\n    38вҶ’\n    39вҶ’**Step 3: Add ProjectDir to Run**\n    40вҶ’\n    41вҶ’In `internal/domain/run.go`, add `ProjectDir string` to the `Run` struct.\n    42вҶ’\n    43вҶ’**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n    44вҶ’\n    45вҶ’Run: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\n    46вҶ’Expected: PASS\n    47вҶ’\n    48вҶ’**Step 5: Write failing test for StepExecution new fields**\n    49вҶ’\n    50вҶ’Add to `internal/domain/run_test.go`:"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70e783a4-e8f4-4ca0-9162-12684b626521","uuid":"53ada720-b358-4d25-adac-9d5caea93eed","timestamp":"2026-03-17T15:35:39.942Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md","content":"# Self-Evolution System Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Implement a daemon-side post-run evolution pipeline that analyzes workflow history to automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows.\n\n**Architecture:** Multi-stage LLM pipeline (Collector вҶ’ Classifier вҶ’ Reflector вҶ’ Executor branches) running in the daemon after each workflow completion. Three executor branches: Prompt Curator (ACE-style), Script Generator (LLM code gen), DSL Mutator (deterministic Go). Changes auto-applied with JSONL audit trail and snapshots.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, SQLite, gRPC, TOML config (`github.com/BurntSushi/toml`), existing LLM agent invocation pattern.\n\n**Design doc:** `docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Extend Domain Types\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/domain/run.go`\n- Modify: `internal/domain/workflow.go`\n- Test: `internal/domain/run_test.go`\n\n**Step 1: Write failing test for Run.ProjectDir**\n\nAdd to `internal/domain/run_test.go`:\n\n```go\nfunc TestRunProjectDir(t *testing.T) {\n\tr := NewRun(\"test-1\", \"develop\")\n\tr.ProjectDir = \"/home/user/project\"\n\tassert.Equal(t, \"/home/user/project\", r.ProjectDir)\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\nExpected: FAIL вҖ” `r.ProjectDir undefined`\n\n**Step 3: Add ProjectDir to Run**\n\nIn `internal/domain/run.go`, add `ProjectDir string` to the `Run` struct.\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/domain/ -run TestRunProjectDir -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Write failing test for StepExecution new fields**\n\nAdd to `internal/domain/run_test.go`:","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":2056}}}
