{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012vy73GtjSQQ5CKowjWxfo5","type":"tool_result","content":"   491вҶ’\n   492вҶ’### Candidate Selection\n   493вҶ’\n   494вҶ’`SelectCandidate` (in `internal/evolution/selector.go`) picks a candidate for\n   495вҶ’the next evolution cycle using a stochastic strategy that balances exploitation\n   496вҶ’and exploration:\n   497вҶ’\n   498вҶ’- **70%** вҖ” pick a random candidate from the Pareto front (exploit known-good\n   499вҶ’  tradeoffs)\n   500вҶ’- **30%** вҖ” pick a random non-front candidate (explore potentially improving\n   501вҶ’  variants)\n   502вҶ’\n   503вҶ’If only one pool has candidates (e.g. all candidates are on the front, or no\n   504вҶ’front candidates exist), selection draws from whichever pool is available.\n   505вҶ’Returns nil when the candidate list is empty, signaling the caller to use the\n   506вҶ’base prompt.\n   507вҶ’\n   508вҶ’### Population Configuration\n   509вҶ’\n   510вҶ’Population-based evolution is controlled by `PopulationConfig`:\n   511вҶ’\n   512вҶ’```go\n   513вҶ’type PopulationConfig struct {\n   514вҶ’    Enabled          bool\n   515вҶ’    MaxCandidates    int"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70e783a4-e8f4-4ca0-9162-12684b626521","uuid":"450d8667-36ed-40ae-a687-5557ed0c1745","timestamp":"2026-03-17T15:36:08.269Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md","content":"\n### Candidate Selection\n\n`SelectCandidate` (in `internal/evolution/selector.go`) picks a candidate for\nthe next evolution cycle using a stochastic strategy that balances exploitation\nand exploration:\n\n- **70%** вҖ” pick a random candidate from the Pareto front (exploit known-good\n  tradeoffs)\n- **30%** вҖ” pick a random non-front candidate (explore potentially improving\n  variants)\n\nIf only one pool has candidates (e.g. all candidates are on the front, or no\nfront candidates exist), selection draws from whichever pool is available.\nReturns nil when the candidate list is empty, signaling the caller to use the\nbase prompt.\n\n### Population Configuration\n\nPopulation-based evolution is controlled by `PopulationConfig`:\n\n```go\ntype PopulationConfig struct {\n    Enabled          bool\n    MaxCandidates    int","numLines":25,"startLine":491,"totalLines":528}}}
